<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/18402APQMLQTPPJPBJSGCJJRVPHSVVCVL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "It's a Wonderful Life";
  schema:description """
	<h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">It's a Wonderful Life</span></span></h2>Adapted for the stage by James W. Rodgers. <span><br/></span>Based on the film by Frank Capra. <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">It’s a Wonderful Life</span> is based on the story “The Greatest Gift” by Philip Van Doren Stern.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>It’s Christmas Eve, 1946, but George Bailey has nothing to celebrate. Backed into a corner and unable to see how any good can come of anything, George is desperate enough to do the worst.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>But that’s when guardian angel Clarence steps in. Clarence is determined to show George that there is a way through the darkness—and, with a little help from his friends—perhaps George might learn that he has far more than he ever thought possible.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Directed by Nicholas Harrison<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This production is presented with the permission of The Greatest Gift Corporation.<span><br/></span>Produced by special arrangement with THE DRAMATIC PUBLISHING COMPANY of Woodstock, Illinois.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.caputheatre.com/\">CapU Theatre Website</a></h2><span><br/></span>Relaxed Performance: Saturday November 14<span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.capilanou.ca/media/capilanouca/student-life/capu-community/blueshore-financial-centre-for-performing-arts/documents/Visual-Story.pdf\">Visual Story for the Theatre</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
