<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/17801ANDDGKKLBMPBRRTQKGLNDCMQGQHV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Mom's the Word: Talkin' Turkey";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">THE HILARIOUS HOLIDAY HIT</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The moms are back in the creative kitchen and ready to turn the “season of giving” into the “season of forgiving.” Enjoy a theatrical feast flavoured with big belly laughs, stuffed with dysfunction, and topped with a soupçon of sarcasm—all served on a platter of naked truth. Using their special recipe of raw humour and humanity, the moms prove that the holidays really are about family, however you define it.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Created by the Mom’s the Word Collective (Jill Daum, Alison Kelly, Robin Nichol, Barbara Pollard & Deborah Williams)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“Hallmark has nothing on this genuinely heartwarming show” —<span class=\"ItalicText\">Stir Vancouver</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">CONTENT ADVISORY</span>⚠️<span><br/></span>This production contains coarse language and mature content and may not be suitable for children. It includes theatrical devices such as strobe lighting and water-based fog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">RUN TIME</span><span><br/></span>Approx. 2h 15m (including one intermission)<span><br/></span>
""";
